 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Foundation test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `load_test` method conducts a static load test consisting of consecutive load levels being applied to the foundation. Symmetric foundations only allow for vertical loads, while non-symmetric foundations can be subjected to shear and moment loads. The loads are applied at the surface level, except in [surface or partially embedded solid foundations](geometry.ipynb#Surface-foundations) where the load is applied at the top of the foundation slab. Positive load values imply:\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"images/signs.png\" alt=\"Load signs.\" width=\"300\">"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Symmetric models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In a [symmetric model](geometry.ipynb#Model-types) loads values are specified by an array, as only vertical loads are possible: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from plxscripting.easy import *\n",
    "import padtest\n",
    "\n",
    "# start server\n",
    "password = \"nicFgr^TtsFm~h~M\"\n",
    "localhostport_input = 10000 \n",
    "localhostport_output = 10001\n",
    "s_i, g_i = new_server('localhost', localhostport_input, password=password) \n",
    "s_o, g_o = new_server('localhost', localhostport_output, password=password)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 3 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.SSolid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# load test\n",
    "testid = 'test A'\n",
    "loads = [-60, 30, -60, 20]\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `plot_test` method generates a figure with the load test. By default, the plot includes all [output locations](geometry.ipynb#Output-locations) and stages of the test:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test A')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test A', location=[0], phase=[0, 1], legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`compression_positive` controls the sign of the vertical force axis. If `True` compression forces are plotted as positive. `pullout_positive` controls the sign of the displacement axis. If `True` then pull-out displacements are positive."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test A', location=[0], phase=[0, 1], legend=True,\n",
    "                compression_positive=False, pullout_positive=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Non-symmetric model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In a [non-symmetric model](geometry.ipynb#Model-types) loads values are specified as 3-element arrays, with their components being Fy, Fx and M. For example, a test consisting of first applying a vertical compressive load, and then a horizontal force and a moment while keeping the compressive force active, and finally removing the horizontal and compressive load is created by:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 3 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.Solid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# load test\n",
    "testid = 'test A'\n",
    "loads = [[-100, 0, 0],  # first stage, apply compressive load\n",
    "         [-100, 40, 100], # second stage, apply horizontal load and moment\n",
    "         [-100, 0, 0]] # Third stage, remove horizontal load and moment\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Results are visualized with the `plot_test` method."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x900 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test A', location=0, legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The displacement and force components to plot are selected with the `force` and `displacement` arguments:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test A', location=0, force=['Fx', 'M'], displacement='ux', legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Failure test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `failure_test` method increases the applied load until the model ceases to converge. A first trial is done using the `load` value provided. If lack of convergence is not achieved, the load is incremented as `load = load_factor * load + load_increment`. The format in which loads are defined for [symmetric and non-symmetric](geometry.ipynb#Model-types) models is the same as in the [load test](#Load-test)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Symmetric model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 3 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.SSolid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Failure test under compression:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'failure - compression'\n",
    "load = -1600\n",
    "model.failure_test(testid, load)"
   ]
  },

    "### Non-symmetric model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,

     "data": {

    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 3 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.Solid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# failure test\n",
    "testid = 'failure'\n",
    "load=[-1600, 300, 1200]\n",
    "model.failure_test(testid, load)\n",
    "\n",
    "model.plot_test('failure', location=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Safety test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `safety_test` creates a safety calculation phase. The converged state from which the safety test starts is set with the [start phase](#Start-phase). Two types of tests are supported: incremental and target tests. In an incremental test the strength reduction factor $\\sum Msf$ is reduced until convergence fails. The reduction step is set with the `Msf` parameter. In a target test the reduction factor is reduced up to a certain target, the target value is set with the `SumMsf` parameter. Results can be visualized with the `plot_safety` method."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 14,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 3 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.SSolid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# create a test to apply a load in the foundation\n",
    "test_id = 'dead load'\n",
    "load = -1600\n",
    "model.load_test(test_id, load)\n",
    "\n",
    "# incremental test\n",
    "test_id = 'safety incremental'\n",
    "start_from='dead load'\n",
    "model.safety_test(test_id, start_from, test='incremental', Msf=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot resutls\n",
    "model.plot_safety_test('safety incremental', location=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For a target test:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 15,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# target test\n",
    "test_id = 'safety target'\n",
    "start_from='dead load'\n",
    "model.safety_test(test_id, start_from, test='target', SumMsf=1.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot resutls\n",
    "model.plot_safety_test('safety target', location=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dynamic load test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `dynamic_test` method applies a dynamic load to the model. The load is defined by a time array and an array with the force components at each instant. The force array has (ncomp, nt) elements, where ncomp is the number of force components and nt is the number of samples across time. In a [solid model](geometry.ipynb#Solid-foundations) only vertical \"Fy\" and horizontal \"Fx\" forces can be applied. In a plate model moments \"M\" can also be applied. The order in which the force components is specified in the force array is Fy, Fx and M. If only Fy is provided, the other components are assumed as 0.\n",
    "\n",
    "[Symmetric](geometry.ipynb#Model-types) models only admit vertical loads. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n",
    "\n",
    "**WARNING**\n",
    "\n",
    "When starting Plaxis remember to configure the license to include *Plaxis 2D Dynamics\". Otherwise, dynamic loads cannot be applied. \n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Package import\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 2 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "soil['RayleighAlpha'] = 0.57 # Rayleight damping alpha parameter\n",
    "soil['RayleighBeta'] = 0.2  # Rayleight damping beta parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.Solid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# dynamic test\n",
    "testid = 'dyn'\n",
    "time = np.arange(0, 3, 0.03)\n",
    "load = -10 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * time)\n",
    "model.dynamic_test(testid, time, load)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `plot_test` function can be used to show the load-displacement across time: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x300 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'dyn'\n",
    "model.plot_test(testid, location=[-1, 0, 1], force='Fy')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `plot_dynamic_test` method shows the variation with time of the displacement and force components."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x800 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 18,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'dyn'\n",
    "model.plot_dynamic_test(testid, location=[-1, 0, 1], legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Displacement and force components are selected with the `displacement` and `force` arguments:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 19,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'dyn'\n",
    "model.plot_dynamic_test(testid, displacement='uy', force='Fy',\n",
    "                        location=[-1, 0, 1], legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Shake test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `shake_test` method conducts a ground shaking test where a displacement time history is imposed on the base of the model. Base excitation of a model requires that interfaces are placed around the edges of the mesh. Although these interfaces are not activated, they increase the mesh density significantly, increasing the computation costs for all tests. Therefore, they are not included in the models by default and should be requested when creating a model by setting the `boundary_interface` parameter to `True`.\n",
    "\n",
    "The difference in meshing density can be appreciated below:\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"images/bounday_interface_mesh.png\" alt=\"Boundary interface effect on mesh.\" width=\"500\">"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n",
    "\n",
    "**WARNING**\n",
    "\n",
    "When starting Plaxis remember to configure the license to include *Plaxis 2D Dynamics\". Otherwise, dynamic boundary conditions cannot be applied. \n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 200x200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 20,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Package import\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 2 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "soil['RayleighAlpha'] = 0.57 # Rayleight damping alpha parameter\n",
    "soil['RayleighBeta'] = 0.2  # Rayleight damping beta parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.Solid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete, boundary_interface=True)\n",
    "model.plot(figsize=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `shake_test` method requires as an input a discretization of the acceleration that will be imposed at the base. The discretization is given by a time array and an acceleration array with as many elements of the time array. If the acceleration array is one dimensional, it is assumed to be the horizontal acceleration. A 2-dimensional array of (2, nt) elements can be provided, where the first row is the horizontal acceleration and the second the vertical acceleration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "testid='shake'\n",
    "time = np.arange(0, 3, 0.03)\n",
    "acceleration = 0.2 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * time)\n",
    "model.shake_test(testid, time, acceleration)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `plot_shake_test` method shows the variation with time of the foundation displacement and base acceleration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x800 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 22,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'shake'\n",
    "model.plot_shake_test(testid, location=[-1, 0, 1], legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Displacement and acceleration components are selected with the `displacement` and `acceleration` arguments:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 23,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "testid = 'shake'\n",
    "model.plot_shake_test(testid, displacement='ux', acceleration='agx',\n",
    "                      location=[-1, 0, 1], legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Surface load"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "In all tests, the `qsurf` parameter imposes a uniformly distributed surface load. This load is applied in a separate phase before the rest of test is conducted. As with the loads acting on the foundation, compression is indicated by a negative value.\n",
    "\n",
    "The following example conducts the same load test with and without a surface load, and compares the results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 200x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 24,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 2 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 2 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.SSolid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "model.plot(figsize=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load test without surface load\n",
    "testid = 'test w/o qsurf'\n",
    "loads = -600\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads)\n",
    "\n",
    "# load test with surface load\n",
    "testid = 'test w. qsurf'\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads, qsurf=-100)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 26,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test w/o qsurf', location=0, displacement='uy', force='Fy')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 27,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test w. qsurf', location=0, \n",
    "                displacement='uy', force='Fy', legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "We can select to plot only the load phase to compare to the case without the surface load. By setting `reset_start` to `True` the plot starts from (0,0). As it can be seen, there is a significant difference in the load-displacement behavior."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 28,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.plot_test('test w. qsurf', location=0, \n",
    "                displacement='uy', force='Fy',\n",
    "                phase='test w. qsurf_stage_0', reset_start=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Start phase"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "By default, all tests types are conducted starting from the construction phase of the model. This can be changed with the `start_from` parameter. If a existing test id is provided, then the new test is performed after the last stage of the selected test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Geometry\n",
    "d = 3 # Foundation depth\n",
    "b = 2 # Foundation width\n",
    "b1 = 0.5 # Foundation column width\n",
    "d1 = 0.5 # Foundation width\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mohr-Coulomb soil material\n",
    "soil = {}\n",
    "soil['SoilModel'] = 'mohr-coulomb'\n",
    "soil[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "soil['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "soil['e0'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['Eref'] = 4e4 # kN\n",
    "soil['nu'] = 0.2\n",
    "soil['cref'] = 0 # kPa\n",
    "soil['phi'] = 35 # deg\n",
    "soil['psi'] = 0 # deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# elastic material for concrete\n",
    "concrete = {}\n",
    "concrete['SoilModel'] = 'elastic'\n",
    "concrete[\"DrainageType\"] = 0\n",
    "concrete['Eref'] =  30e6  # kPa\n",
    "concrete['nu'] = 0.4 #\n",
    "concrete['gammaSat'] = 20 # kN/m3\n",
    "concrete['gammaUnsat'] = 17 # kN/m3\n",
    "\n",
    "# build model\n",
    "model = padtest.SSolid(s_i, g_i, g_o, b, d, b1, d1, soil, concrete)\n",
    "\n",
    "# load test\n",
    "testid = 'test A'\n",
    "loads = [-60, 30, -40]\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "To start from the last phase of `'test A'`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load test\n",
    "testid = 'test B'\n",
    "loads = [40]\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads, start_from='test A')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "An specific stage of a test can be selected by providing a tuple with the test id and the stage number (starting from 0). For example, `'test A'` hast 3 stages, corresponding to the -60, +30, -40 load values. If the new test is to start from the +30 stage, then `start_from` should be set to `('test A', 1)`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load test\n",
    "testid = 'test C'\n",
    "loads = [40]\n",
    "model.load_test(testid, loads, start_from=('test A', 1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Failure and safety test cannot be used as starting stages of a new test, since the model has ceased to converge."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Delete test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "The `delete_test` method removes tests from both the results table and Plaxis. If `delete_phases` is set to `False` the calculation phases in Plaxis are kept."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model.delete_test('test C')"
   ]
  }
